<h1>HTML COMMENT</h1>

<p>HTML comments are not displayed in the browser, but they can help document your HTML source code.</p>

<hr>

<h2>HTML Comment Tags</h2>

<p>You can add comments to your HTML code using the following syntax:</p>

<pre>
<code>
&lt;!-- This is a comment --&gt;
</code>
</pre>

<p>Comments are helpful for explaining code, organizing sections, or leaving notes for other developers.</p>

<hr>

<h2>Add Comments</h2>

<p>With comments, you can place reminders or explanations in your code without affecting the visual output.</p>

<pre>
<code>
&lt;!-- This is a comment --&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a paragraph.&lt;/p&gt;
</code>
</pre>

<p>The comment will not be visible in the browser.</p>

<hr>

<h2>Hide Content</h2>

<p>You can also use comments to hide content that you don’t want to be visible temporarily:</p>

<pre>
<code>
&lt;p&gt;This is a visible paragraph.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;!-- &lt;p&gt;This is a hidden paragraph.&lt;/p&gt; --&gt;
</code>
</pre>

<p>Only the first paragraph will be shown.</p>

<hr>

<h2>Browser Output</h2>

<p>Here’s how the browser renders the code:</p>

<p>This is a visible paragraph.</p>

<!-- <p>This is a hidden paragraph.</p> -->

<hr>

<h2>End of Page</h2>

<p>That’s how HTML comments work. They're essential for code organization and team development.</p>

</body>
</center>
